    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Large-format cameras that have adjustable front and rear standards mounted on rails and connected by bellows. Moving these standards independently of each other allows the photographer greater control of sharpness across the image plane, subject distance, and perspective.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
